About 180 South Africans have died and just under a thousand infected since the beginning of the outbreak as a result of contaminated ready-to-eat meat products. 

The country's health authorities recently declared the source of the outbreak as the food factory, Enterprise in city of Polokwane. This prompted a national and international recall of the facility's food products such as polony, cold meats, sausages and viennas. 

